cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a patch-based approach using CNN for segmentation of nuclei in single cell images, and a transfer learning-based approach for classification using both segmented as well as full single cell images. These techniques are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed algorithms for information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) applications. Additionally, the paper deals with medical image analysis (cs.MM) specifically for PAP-smear images.
